TLDR;
Even if you make an xbox account and link it to steam no promise it works or lets you play with friends. Google it, 2 years no resolution.

Multiplayer may or may not be good we will never know since Xbox continues to make crossplay painful in a delusion of control. I didn't play it solo because that's not why I bought it and to buy a game with friends and waste an hour jumping thru hoops to return the game because playing with each other was such a chore is all the review you should need.

Be Me.
->Spend over 30 hours in-game ;
->Get 12 survivors at the base ;
->Have atleast 30 sacks of each type of resource ;
->Character and me both get a little tired for playing continuously ; 
->Try to takedown a plague heart alone ; 
-> Mission Failed miserably ;
-> Character Died ;
-> Everyone at homebase gets depressed ;
-> People start leaving ;
-> Resources get depleted at faster rate ; 
-> My last community member died 
-> Game Over.
-> Bust the fattest nut I have ever.

Better than any cock and ball torture I can get........
10/10
